1
00:00:09,146 --> 00:00:13,187
SIX YEARS EARLIER

2
00:00:13,271 --> 00:00:15,271
[speeding car approaching]

3
00:00:16,146 --> 00:00:18,146
[tires squealing]

4
00:00:23,271 --> 00:00:26,312
- [rap music playing on stereo]
- You feel that beat there, little man?

5
00:00:26,396 --> 00:00:28,229
Feel it! Move!

6
00:00:28,812 --> 00:00:30,479
Ahh! Feel it!

7
00:00:34,729 --> 00:00:37,437
Mm. Little man, take that.

8
00:00:37,521 --> 00:00:39,312
My man!

9
00:00:40,812 --> 00:00:42,062
Cut it out, Nat!

10
00:00:42,646 --> 00:00:45,104
[Nat] Relax, I got this!
Dance, little man!

11
00:00:45,187 --> 00:00:46,187
This is too fast!

12
00:00:46,271 --> 00:00:49,979
Well, I'm the one driving to Mama's
and I say you're both being losers!

13
00:00:51,104 --> 00:00:52,187
[Annabelle] Let us out, now!

14
00:00:52,271 --> 00:00:53,812
[screams] Nat!

15
00:00:54,896 --> 00:00:56,896
[loud crash]

16
00:00:58,521 --> 00:01:00,521
[bittersweet music playing]

17
00:01:15,354 --> 00:01:17,437
Where is Dylan, Mama?

18
00:01:20,396 --> 00:01:21,604
At the morgue.

19
00:01:24,687 --> 00:01:26,187
What happened, Annabelle?

20
00:01:27,562 --> 00:01:28,562
Uh…

21
00:01:30,479 --> 00:01:33,062
Did Nathanaël murder my boy, Annabelle?

22
00:01:33,146 --> 00:01:34,354
[softly] Mama…

23
00:01:36,812 --> 00:01:38,104
What happened?

24
00:01:38,854 --> 00:01:41,354
Tell me what happened Annabelle
or the police will.

25
00:01:41,437 --> 00:01:42,979
I didn't do anything.

26
00:01:43,062 --> 00:01:45,771
There was a stray on the road.
I tried to avoid it.

27
00:01:47,937 --> 00:01:49,437
Was there an animal on the road?

28
00:01:51,104 --> 00:01:52,312
No.

29
00:01:55,396 --> 00:01:57,021
[Nat] Mama, I swear it was an accident.

30
00:01:58,687 --> 00:02:00,687
[bittersweet music continues]

31
00:02:03,604 --> 00:02:06,312
We were playing around
and the little demon came out of nowhere.

32
00:02:06,396 --> 00:02:07,979
- It wasn't my fault.
- Enough, Nat.

33
00:02:10,396 --> 00:02:11,229
You're sad?

34
00:02:15,812 --> 00:02:18,854
You'll forever live
with a heavy sadness all alone.

35
00:02:19,687 --> 00:02:21,687
No one can help you anymore.

36
00:02:22,604 --> 00:02:23,604
[Nat] What?

37
00:02:25,021 --> 00:02:28,062
You'll never see your brothers
or sisters ever again.

38
00:02:30,354 --> 00:02:32,854
You are no longer welcome in my house.

39
00:02:35,562 --> 00:02:37,562
[bittersweet music continues]

40
00:02:41,021 --> 00:02:44,021
- [music fades]
- [insects chirping softly]

41
00:02:46,312 --> 00:02:48,646
[Kingsley groaning softly]

42
00:02:53,479 --> 00:02:56,604
[Kingsley softly] Take this.
Hide the packages.

43
00:02:56,687 --> 00:02:57,854
[Léo softly] Where?

44
00:02:58,646 --> 00:03:01,271
- Who makes your bed? Cass or you?
- No one does.

45
00:03:01,354 --> 00:03:03,479
- Then put it there.
- Okay.

46
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,187
[Kingsley wincing]

47
00:03:18,229 --> 00:03:19,604
Fuck.

48
00:03:21,687 --> 00:03:24,146
[groaning softly]

49
00:03:27,354 --> 00:03:28,521
What are you doing?

50
00:03:29,271 --> 00:03:31,854
- Nothing, go back to bed.
- What happened?

51
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:34,937
[exhales] Nothing, don't worry.

52
00:03:35,021 --> 00:03:37,396
- You need a hospital, King.
- No way.

53
00:03:37,896 --> 00:03:40,354
- You might lose that leg.
- No hospital.

54
00:03:41,271 --> 00:03:42,271
[Cassandra sighs]

55
00:03:51,229 --> 00:03:52,937
[Kingsley wincing]

56
00:04:02,854 --> 00:04:04,271
- Apply pressure.
- [groans]

57
00:04:06,979 --> 00:04:10,021
Wrap this around your leg.
You'll still need stitches.

58
00:04:45,937 --> 00:04:48,937
[thrilling music playing]

59
00:04:59,062 --> 00:05:01,146
The white rooster. That's him there.

60
00:05:02,479 --> 00:05:03,479
[man] I know him.

61
00:05:04,479 --> 00:05:05,604
You do?

62
00:05:06,312 --> 00:05:09,396
Yeah, back in the day,
he'd go fishing with my old man.

63
00:05:10,229 --> 00:05:12,146
[thrilling music continues]

64
00:05:17,229 --> 00:05:18,521
Fast, follow.

65
00:05:19,396 --> 00:05:22,312
[thrilling music continues]

66
00:05:31,187 --> 00:05:32,771
Hey, kids! Don't fuck with me!

67
00:05:32,854 --> 00:05:35,187
I need to get home!
I have my old rooster with me.

68
00:05:35,271 --> 00:05:37,646
- Hey! Let go! Stop!
- [rooster clucks]

69
00:05:37,729 --> 00:05:40,562
Joé, are you out of your damn mind?
What are you doing?

70
00:05:40,646 --> 00:05:42,312
Hey, let go! Are you crazy?

71
00:05:42,812 --> 00:05:44,687
[Kylian] Grab the rooster, grab it.

72
00:05:53,562 --> 00:05:55,104
[music stops]

73
00:06:20,229 --> 00:06:21,062
See you, Milord.

74
00:06:21,771 --> 00:06:22,771
Hold on.

75
00:06:31,312 --> 00:06:32,604
[man] Stop moving.

76
00:06:34,771 --> 00:06:36,187
What the hell is this?

77
00:06:45,229 --> 00:06:47,271
[in Spanish] Cockfighter!
You stole from me.

78
00:06:47,354 --> 00:06:49,062
And now you're a damn snitch too, huh?

79
00:06:49,937 --> 00:06:53,021
Little bitch.
You think you're safe in your country?

80
00:06:53,604 --> 00:06:56,021
Guys, I'm offering
a reward of 1,000 dollars…

81
00:06:56,521 --> 00:06:58,479
to whoever brings me that son of a bitch.

82
00:06:58,562 --> 00:07:01,729
Screw that white rooster of yours,
you Martinican fucker.

83
00:07:05,021 --> 00:07:08,187
[in English] He's employed, I think,
by your Venezuelan friends.

84
00:07:09,437 --> 00:07:10,687
Maybe.

85
00:07:11,854 --> 00:07:14,062
He has a white combat rooster.
He's real easy to spot.

86
00:07:15,729 --> 00:07:17,771
[man] Yeah, this guy talks too much.

87
00:07:18,354 --> 00:07:20,687
So you're doing this for the money?

88
00:07:20,771 --> 00:07:23,187
Nah, it's not that.
I want to meet the cartel.

89
00:07:23,771 --> 00:07:24,771
[chuckles softly]

90
00:07:25,771 --> 00:07:29,562
That's bold of you, Milord.
Those men don't play any games.

91
00:07:35,729 --> 00:07:37,354
I'll be contacting you.

92
00:07:40,062 --> 00:07:41,104
Uh…

93
00:07:42,229 --> 00:07:43,479
This man belongs to you.

94
00:07:44,187 --> 00:07:45,562
Keep him for now.

95
00:07:49,229 --> 00:07:53,271
I hope you thought this through,
'cause this is rubbing me the wrong way.

96
00:07:55,729 --> 00:07:57,021
Where you get that video, bro?

97
00:07:57,104 --> 00:07:59,437
On social media,
you just need to look for it.

98
00:08:00,187 --> 00:08:01,729
[rooster clucks softly]

99
00:08:16,562 --> 00:08:20,271
Stop it. Chill out, guys.
It looks bad, but it's fine.

100
00:08:20,854 --> 00:08:21,979
Where's Léo?

101
00:08:22,062 --> 00:08:23,062
He's sleeping.

102
00:08:23,146 --> 00:08:24,604
- Let him rest.
- Go wake that child.

103
00:08:24,687 --> 00:08:26,854
We got in late last night.
Leave him alone.

104
00:08:27,479 --> 00:08:28,479
He's going to school.

105
00:08:28,562 --> 00:08:31,062
- Wake Léo, would you?
- [rooster crowing]

106
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,021
How are you?

107
00:08:34,646 --> 00:08:35,646
What's this?

108
00:08:35,729 --> 00:08:37,021
I'm babysitting.

109
00:08:38,979 --> 00:08:39,979
What happened?

110
00:08:40,062 --> 00:08:42,687
What happened is that he got the children
mixed up in his games.

111
00:08:42,771 --> 00:08:45,646
- I came first to the grown ups, didn't I?
- Is that what you have to say?

112
00:08:45,729 --> 00:08:47,604
- Uh, yeah.
- But who did this to you?

113
00:08:47,687 --> 00:08:50,729
- Don't think you can question me.
- I'm asking the questions, bro.

114
00:08:50,812 --> 00:08:52,396
Move, we're stepping out to talk.

115
00:08:52,479 --> 00:08:54,562
- I'm not going anywhere.
- Get up.

116
00:08:54,646 --> 00:08:57,646
Go on outside then. You're going alone.

117
00:08:57,729 --> 00:09:00,396
[clicks tongue] Wow, that smells heavenly.
Can I have some, Cass?

118
00:09:03,104 --> 00:09:05,146
You guys, on the other hand, are assholes.

119
00:09:05,229 --> 00:09:06,896
This little guy needs sleep.

120
00:09:06,979 --> 00:09:08,354
Look how exhausted he is.

121
00:09:08,437 --> 00:09:10,771
- Poor thing!
- I'm gonna fuckin' bust your face.

122
00:09:10,854 --> 00:09:13,146
Go ahead, brother. Indulge yourself.

123
00:09:13,229 --> 00:09:15,729
Kids, go outside for now
and play while we speak.

124
00:09:18,146 --> 00:09:19,812
[Mathis] You're in trouble.

125
00:09:21,937 --> 00:09:24,396
- Léo, last night, what did you do?
- Don't you say a word.

126
00:09:25,104 --> 00:09:27,687
- Cass, may I have one?
- Léo, I'm asking you a question.

127
00:09:27,771 --> 00:09:29,187
Shouldn't you be asking him?

128
00:09:29,271 --> 00:09:32,062
Hey, don't forget that I'm the adult.
I'm the one asking questions.

129
00:09:32,146 --> 00:09:34,937
- Answer me, please.
- Marvin, stop torturing him like this.

130
00:09:35,021 --> 00:09:37,229
King, you best quit disrespecting me now!

131
00:09:37,312 --> 00:09:39,271
[Ambre] Hey, Marvin, enough! Cut it out!

132
00:09:40,979 --> 00:09:42,062
[Marvin] Wow.

133
00:09:42,146 --> 00:09:44,187
Léo, what did he
force you to do last night?

134
00:09:44,271 --> 00:09:47,562
- Nothing, we just stole some drugs.
- Tell me how he hurt himself.

135
00:09:47,646 --> 00:09:49,354
It was Vincez that stabbed him.

136
00:09:50,021 --> 00:09:51,896
- Vincez?
- Yeah, the guy who invited us.

137
00:09:51,979 --> 00:09:53,312
But he suddenly got very mean.

138
00:09:53,396 --> 00:09:55,479
Vincez, SherKhan's cousin?

139
00:09:55,562 --> 00:09:57,854
Léo, stop. [clicks tongue]
How do you know Vincez, bro?

140
00:09:57,937 --> 00:09:58,979
Fucking stop.

141
00:09:59,479 --> 00:10:02,021
- Continue, Léo. I'm listening to you.
- He was gonna kill King.

142
00:10:02,104 --> 00:10:04,771
- And so?
- And so I knocked him out, that's all.

143
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,729
Knocked who out?
No way you knocked him out!

144
00:10:06,812 --> 00:10:07,812
Léo, cut it.

145
00:10:07,896 --> 00:10:10,937
I shot that motherfucker. I saved King.

146
00:10:11,021 --> 00:10:13,562
Boom, in his face.
He won't mess with the Lafleur family.

147
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:15,521
Please say you are joking.

148
00:10:16,021 --> 00:10:18,062
- Wait, did you have a gun?
- No gun.

149
00:10:18,146 --> 00:10:21,479
He's mixed up in the head right now.
He's all shook up, yeah. Ignore him.

150
00:10:21,562 --> 00:10:23,146
[Ambre] Was it Mama's gun?

151
00:10:25,104 --> 00:10:27,687
What gun did he fire with? Was it Mama's?

152
00:10:35,437 --> 00:10:36,979
You aren't up yet?

153
00:10:43,771 --> 00:10:46,687
It's almost half a million. Consider that.

154
00:10:47,187 --> 00:10:49,271
You mean you swiped half a million?

155
00:10:49,354 --> 00:10:51,771
I told you already
that I don't answer to you.

156
00:10:51,854 --> 00:10:53,312
We all answer to someone.

157
00:10:53,396 --> 00:10:55,979
You stole SherKhan's money
and shot his cousin?

158
00:10:56,062 --> 00:10:58,396
- You made off with how much?
- There's so many packages.

159
00:10:58,479 --> 00:11:01,021
- [Kylian] Where are these packages?
- Don't speak, Léo.

160
00:11:01,104 --> 00:11:04,104
- Confession's for church.
- Mama's gun is now gone.

161
00:11:06,604 --> 00:11:08,396
I put Mama's gun in my bag.

162
00:11:08,896 --> 00:11:10,646
[Marvin] Fuck,
did you shoot someone, King?

163
00:11:10,729 --> 00:11:12,729
You mean you'd rob them unarmed?

164
00:11:12,812 --> 00:11:14,979
He shot nobody. Don't twist it.

165
00:11:15,062 --> 00:11:16,937
I'm the one that saved you
and shot the pistol.

166
00:11:17,021 --> 00:11:18,521
You allowed Léo to use Mama's gun?

167
00:11:21,312 --> 00:11:23,687
Don't get back up, King.
I'll knock your ass out.

168
00:11:25,979 --> 00:11:27,646
[doorbell ringing]

169
00:11:34,229 --> 00:11:36,437
[woman] Hello! Are you Marvin Lafleur?

170
00:11:36,521 --> 00:11:37,562
Yes, what is it?

171
00:11:37,646 --> 00:11:40,062
I'm here on behalf
of the juvenile court to investigate.

172
00:11:40,646 --> 00:11:43,479
To see how you all are doing
after your mother's passing.

173
00:11:44,229 --> 00:11:45,437
May I come in?

174
00:11:50,146 --> 00:11:52,437
We were about to head out for groceries.

175
00:12:12,187 --> 00:12:14,271
[lighter clicking]

176
00:12:16,312 --> 00:12:18,271
We're gonna be changing that.

177
00:12:23,979 --> 00:12:25,937
[rooster crowing]

178
00:12:28,396 --> 00:12:29,396
Is that a rooster?

179
00:12:33,854 --> 00:12:36,187
It was Mama's. We're gonna be selling it.

180
00:12:55,104 --> 00:12:57,521
Oh, I injured myself
while fixing the garden.

181
00:13:01,437 --> 00:13:02,646
Who sleeps here?

182
00:13:02,729 --> 00:13:04,062
It's the kids' room.

183
00:13:04,146 --> 00:13:07,521
I'd like to speak with the children.
Thaïs as well, please.

184
00:13:09,812 --> 00:13:12,104
- Hello, children.
- [kids] Hello.

185
00:13:15,229 --> 00:13:16,896
Could I sit next to you?

186
00:13:19,187 --> 00:13:20,187
Well, may I?

187
00:13:31,521 --> 00:13:33,604
Tell me who's looking after you lately?

188
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:35,187
Cassandra.

189
00:13:35,271 --> 00:13:38,146
- Is she the oldest sister?
- No, Annabelle is.

190
00:13:38,229 --> 00:13:40,729
She's very tired right now.

191
00:13:40,812 --> 00:13:42,229
She's been crying today.

192
00:13:45,479 --> 00:13:49,687
- [Ambre] What do you think will happen?
- Foster homes for the kids, probably.

193
00:13:49,771 --> 00:13:52,062
- What?
- That's not possible.

194
00:13:52,146 --> 00:13:53,146
Completely impossible.

195
00:13:53,229 --> 00:13:54,479
Hold on.

196
00:13:55,062 --> 00:13:56,562
Can they just remove them like that?

197
00:13:56,646 --> 00:13:59,646
Yes, if they think we're negligent,
or believe that the kids are in danger.

198
00:13:59,729 --> 00:14:01,104
But they are in danger.

199
00:14:01,187 --> 00:14:03,479
- Right, King?
- Damn, you won't drop it, will you?

200
00:14:03,562 --> 00:14:05,854
Go fuck yourself, bro. Seriously.

201
00:14:05,937 --> 00:14:08,354
I'm not finished with you, King.
Just wait.

202
00:14:08,437 --> 00:14:10,979
I think you want them to be taken,
don't you?

203
00:14:11,062 --> 00:14:13,771
Remove all us inconveniences
from the peaceful life you want.

204
00:14:13,854 --> 00:14:17,104
Fuck off, Kingsley,
or I'll break your damn face.

205
00:14:20,354 --> 00:14:23,146
What? Anybody else want to speak?

206
00:14:23,229 --> 00:14:25,896
Does this concern only us? Hmm?

207
00:14:27,229 --> 00:14:29,979
Start speaking up.
You're all a part of this family.

208
00:14:30,979 --> 00:14:34,104
Did I help with killing someone?

209
00:14:35,354 --> 00:14:36,479
Killing?

210
00:14:37,229 --> 00:14:38,646
No one died.

211
00:14:38,729 --> 00:14:42,021
Don't panic, Cass. It'll be okay.
No one knows I was there.

212
00:14:45,937 --> 00:14:47,604
You got anything to say?

213
00:14:48,854 --> 00:14:52,521
Truthfully, King,
I think robbing SherKhan was a lousy idea.

214
00:14:52,604 --> 00:14:54,271
[Ambre] It doesn't help us at all.

215
00:14:54,354 --> 00:14:56,812
He's dragging us down. Just forget him.

216
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,271
I've got to go work.

217
00:14:58,354 --> 00:15:00,229
You got work too, Kiki.

218
00:15:01,104 --> 00:15:02,854
You also goin' to work.

219
00:15:02,937 --> 00:15:04,979
And you too, sunshine.

220
00:15:05,062 --> 00:15:08,979
If we act as a team,
we can provide for the family honestly.

221
00:15:09,062 --> 00:15:12,187
[sarcastically] Okay. Super. Perfect.

222
00:15:13,062 --> 00:15:14,062
Best of luck.

223
00:15:19,062 --> 00:15:22,479
- [sighs softly]
- [pensive music playing]

224
00:15:26,604 --> 00:15:29,604
- [pensive music continues]
- [monitor beeping softly]

225
00:15:33,812 --> 00:15:34,896
Jerome.

226
00:15:36,062 --> 00:15:37,146
[laughs softly]

227
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:39,646
We were looking last night for you.

228
00:15:40,479 --> 00:15:43,146
I spoke with your man
at the surveillance center.

229
00:15:44,312 --> 00:15:47,396
- [man] You don't know what happened?
- Nah! Do you?

230
00:15:48,146 --> 00:15:50,229
We'll find out, because you're gonna tell.

231
00:15:52,187 --> 00:15:54,062
Depends on who talk first.

232
00:15:55,396 --> 00:15:58,229
I suggest you stay on my good side
and lay low.

233
00:15:58,312 --> 00:15:59,979
Or you can deal with Ducos instead, hmm?

234
00:16:02,896 --> 00:16:04,646
Find the fuckers that did this.

235
00:16:15,271 --> 00:16:17,729
- [kid laughing]
- SherKhan took a bad beating, guys!

236
00:16:17,812 --> 00:16:19,271
- No way!
- [laughing]

237
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:21,396
[girl on phone] Oh, but wait.

238
00:16:21,479 --> 00:16:22,979
That's not even the worst of it.

239
00:16:23,062 --> 00:16:24,812
His cousin found
the thugs that robbed him,

240
00:16:24,896 --> 00:16:27,646
and was shot
while the robbers escaped unharmed.

241
00:16:27,729 --> 00:16:28,812
[kids laughing on video]

242
00:16:29,771 --> 00:16:32,146
That's the type of buzz
we have to stay away from.

243
00:16:32,229 --> 00:16:34,229
Just look on as a spectator.

244
00:16:35,229 --> 00:16:37,979
- Your brother's not part of this, right?
- Why would you say that?

245
00:16:38,062 --> 00:16:39,396
He has a reputation as a thief.

246
00:16:39,479 --> 00:16:42,396
That's impossible.
We were at home together.

247
00:16:42,479 --> 00:16:44,687
[laughs softly]
Is that your story for the cops?

248
00:16:45,479 --> 00:16:49,146
Look, our mother was buried last week,
so we're grieving as a family.

249
00:16:49,229 --> 00:16:51,187
We lean on each other for support.

250
00:16:54,729 --> 00:16:56,021
You're orphans.

251
00:16:57,104 --> 00:16:58,646
It's not my problem…

252
00:16:58,729 --> 00:17:01,229
except if your brother
and you are affected.

253
00:17:01,312 --> 00:17:02,687
Then it's my problem.

254
00:17:03,396 --> 00:17:06,062
Make sure the container is prepared for us
before we move the product.

255
00:17:06,146 --> 00:17:07,979
- Understood?
- Watch how you talk to me.

256
00:17:08,854 --> 00:17:11,271
I said it would be ready, so it will be.

257
00:17:13,437 --> 00:17:14,521
Get out now.

258
00:17:18,771 --> 00:17:21,229
[door opens and closes]

259
00:17:21,312 --> 00:17:23,312
[inmates chattering]

260
00:17:25,312 --> 00:17:28,979
DUCOS CORRECTIONAL FACILITY

261
00:17:35,104 --> 00:17:37,979
- Are you serious? You always hound me.
- You stop.

262
00:17:40,771 --> 00:17:41,979
The children?

263
00:17:43,646 --> 00:17:45,562
The kids might not understand yet.

264
00:17:47,062 --> 00:17:49,896
They're lucky to have many siblings.
It will help ease things.

265
00:17:52,729 --> 00:17:55,104
Hey now, son. Please don't cry.

266
00:17:55,687 --> 00:17:56,771
Stop crying.

267
00:17:57,896 --> 00:17:59,979
Don't weep like a woman. Man up, brother.

268
00:18:02,021 --> 00:18:03,062
[Kylian] Hmm.

269
00:18:06,062 --> 00:18:07,354
My mom passed too.

270
00:18:07,437 --> 00:18:09,479
You're not alone, brother.

271
00:18:09,562 --> 00:18:13,146
Life just isn't fair. End of story.

272
00:18:14,021 --> 00:18:16,979
I empathize with you,
your siblings pain, I truly do,

273
00:18:17,854 --> 00:18:20,354
but this will transform you to a man.

274
00:18:22,229 --> 00:18:23,312
Okay?

275
00:18:23,937 --> 00:18:26,562
Kylian, you've just gotta
take life by the balls

276
00:18:26,646 --> 00:18:28,312
or it will fuck you up.

277
00:18:32,187 --> 00:18:34,646
Now, choose, will you step up or what?

278
00:18:36,937 --> 00:18:38,104
Maybe.

279
00:18:38,979 --> 00:18:41,479
Be firmer. Otherwise, life will beat you.

280
00:18:43,062 --> 00:18:47,146
They'll separate us from Thaïs,
Nolan, even Mathis.

281
00:18:47,687 --> 00:18:49,396
Maybe that's what's best for them.

282
00:18:49,479 --> 00:18:52,771
Their father did pass away
many years ago, right?

283
00:18:52,854 --> 00:18:55,521
Perhaps they'll find a foster family.
Think about it.

284
00:18:56,021 --> 00:18:57,021
No.

285
00:18:57,771 --> 00:18:59,062
Mama wanted us to be together.

286
00:19:02,562 --> 00:19:04,312
Okay, and the older kids?

287
00:19:05,521 --> 00:19:08,062
Are they missing in action?
What the fuck are they doing?

288
00:19:08,146 --> 00:19:10,771
Marvin, King, Annabelle,
what have they done?

289
00:19:11,854 --> 00:19:13,604
Dad, what can we do here?

290
00:19:14,146 --> 00:19:16,729
What can we do? Mind your own shit.

291
00:19:16,812 --> 00:19:17,854
Okay?

292
00:19:17,937 --> 00:19:19,187
Focus on you.

293
00:19:19,271 --> 00:19:20,979
And forget about helping the kids.

294
00:19:22,187 --> 00:19:23,187
Okay?

295
00:19:23,271 --> 00:19:24,854
They'll live their lives.

296
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:29,062
Also, I sincerely hope
you didn't come here for a handout.

297
00:19:29,146 --> 00:19:30,479
I got no money.

298
00:19:31,479 --> 00:19:33,146
Nah, money's no issue.

299
00:19:34,729 --> 00:19:36,979
